question:
District category contains Learning Hub, High School Zone, and Manufacturing District.
Supermarkets category contains E.Leclerc, Food Lion, and Hungryroot.
Product category contains Croissants, Cottage Cheese, and Canned Tomatoes.
The number of each E.Leclerc 's Cottage Cheese equals the sum of each Hungryroot 's Product, each Manufacturing District 's Hungryroot, and each Hungryroot 's Croissants.
The number of each Hungryroot 's Cottage Cheese equals each Learning Hub 's E.Leclerc.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Food Lion equals 7.
The number of each E.Leclerc 's Croissants equals 22 times each Manufacturing District 's E.Leclerc.
The number of each Hungryroot 's Croissants equals each High School Zone 's E.Leclerc.
The number of each Learning Hub 's Food Lion equals 18 times each Learning Hub 's E.Leclerc.
The number of each Food Lion 's Cottage Cheese equals 13.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's E.Leclerc equals 1.
The number of each E.Leclerc 's Canned Tomatoes equals each Hungryroot 's Cottage Cheese.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Hungryroot equals the sum of each Manufacturing District 's E.Leclerc and each High School Zone 's Food Lion.
The number of each Food Lion 's Canned Tomatoes equals 18 times each High School Zone 's E.Leclerc.
The number of each High School Zone 's Food Lion equals 19 more than each Manufacturing District 's E.Leclerc.
The number of each Learning Hub 's E.Leclerc equals 13.
The number of each High School Zone 's E.Leclerc equals the sum of each Learning Hub 's E.Leclerc and each Food Lion 's Cottage Cheese.
How many Cottage Cheese does Hungryroot have?
solution:
Define each Learning Hub 's E.Leclerc as o; So o = 13.
Define each Hungryroot 's Cottage Cheese as s; So s = o = 13.
